The paper focuses on robot-assisted surgeries and proposes a deep learning model for estimating the current state of surgical tasks based on multiple data sources, including kinematics and vision. This work involves robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it aims to improve the automation of surgical tasks through the use of deep learning models.
